<subSubSection id="C3686521FFD7034503A5F9E79507AD71" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="2474" pageId="3" pageNumber="2473" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BCD36AAFFD7034203A5F9E7962BAA38" blockId="3.[160,1155,1633,1728]" box="[160,276,1633,1659]" pageId="3" pageNumber="2473">
<emphasis id="B906EAB8FFD7034203A5F9E7962BAA38" bold="true" box="[160,276,1633,1659]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="2473">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCD36AAFFD7034503A5F9039507AD71" blockId="3.[160,1155,1633,1728]" lastBlockId="4.[160,1155,142,306]" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="2474" pageId="3" pageNumber="2473">
Body elliptical, measuring 70–100 × 
<quantity id="4C8A9B4FFFD70342012AF90395A2AADD" box="[559,669,1669,1694]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.25" metricValueMax="5.0" metricValueMin="3.5" pageId="3" pageNumber="2473" unit="mm" value="42.5" valueMax="50.0" valueMin="35.0">35–50 µm</quantity>
in vivo. Two macronuclear nodules and one to four micronuclei. Contractile vacuole located approximately at mid-body. Adoral zone composed of 22–28 membranelles. Constantly 16 frontoventral-transverse cirri with three transverse cirri closely positioned and four frontoventral cirri arranged in triangle. One left and one right marginal row comprising 15–21 and 19–24 cirri, respectively. Four dorsal kineties and two dorsomarginal kineties. Three caudal cirri. Resting cyst with polygon wrinkles on the surface. Soil habitat.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3686521FFD0034503A5FEE496DCAEFA" pageId="4" pageNumber="2474" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph id="8BCD36AAFFD0034503A5FEE49609AD3F" blockId="4.[160,1155,354,449]" box="[160,310,354,380]" pageId="4" pageNumber="2474">
<emphasis id="B906EAB8FFD0034503A5FEE49609AD3F" bold="true" box="[160,310,354,380]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="2474">
<typeStatus id="54C98808FFD0034503A5FEE497E7AD3F" box="[160,216,354,380]" pageId="4" pageNumber="2474">Type</typeStatus>
locality
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCD36AAFFD0034503A5FE009566AD82" blockId="4.[160,1155,354,449]" pageId="4" pageNumber="2474">
Collected from the surface soil (
<emphasis id="B906EAB8FFD003450125FE009514ADDC" box="[544,555,390,415]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="2474">c</emphasis>
. 
<quantity id="4C8A9B4FFFD003450138FE00959CADDC" box="[573,675,390,415]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" metricValueMax="10.0" metricValueMin="0.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="2474" unit="cm" value="5.0" valueMax="10.0" valueMin="0.0">0–10 cm</quantity>
) on a hill in Jiangjunshan ancient town (34º01 
<emphasis id="B906EAB8FFD0034503EDFE2F97D1AD83" bold="true" box="[232,238,425,448]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="2474">ʹ</emphasis>
19 
<emphasis id="B906EAB8FFD00345020CFE2F9630AD83" bold="true" box="[265,271,425,448]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="2474">ʹ</emphasis>
’N; 108º65 
<emphasis id="B906EAB8FFD003450284FE2F96B8AD83" bold="true" box="[385,391,425,448]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="2474">ʹ</emphasis>
51 
<emphasis id="B906EAB8FFD0034502A7FE2F9697AD83" bold="true" box="[418,424,425,448]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="2474">ʹ</emphasis>
’E), Xi’an, 
<collectingCountry id="F365763AFFD003450117FE2E956AAD82" box="[530,597,424,449]" name="China" pageId="4" pageNumber="2474">China</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCD36AAFFD0034503A5FE7496B7AE4F" blockId="4.[160,1156,498,697]" box="[160,392,498,524]" pageId="4" pageNumber="2474">
<emphasis id="B906EAB8FFD0034503A5FE7496B7AE4F" bold="true" box="[160,392,498,524]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="2474">Deposition of slides</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCD36AAFFD0034503A5FD9396DCAEFA" blockId="4.[160,1156,498,697]" pageId="4" pageNumber="2474">
The protargol slide (No. LZ2016041702A) containing the 
<typeStatus id="54C98808FFD00345000AFD93944EAE6D" box="[783,881,533,558]" pageId="4" pageNumber="2474">holotype</typeStatus>
specimen (
<figureCitation id="13492A2FFFD0034500F4FD93936FAE6D" box="[1009,1104,533,558]" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="4.[160,225,1528,1551]" captionTargetBox="[167,1150,933,1493]" captionTargetId="figure-186@4.[163,1153,932,1496]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figure 1. Morphology of Sterkiella paratricirrata n. sp. from life (a, b) and after protargol staining (c, d). (a) Ventral view of a representative individual. (b) Resting cyst. (c, d) Ventral (c) and dorsal (d) view of the holotype specimen, showing the infraciliature and nuclear apparatus. AZM, adoral zone of membranelles; CC, caudal cirri; CV, contractile vacuole; LMR, left marginal row; Ma, macronuclear nodules; Mi, micronuclei; RMR, right marginal row; I/1, II/3, III/3, frontal cirri; II/2, buccal cirrus; III/2, IV/ 3, VI/3, VI/4, frontoventral cirri; IV/2, V/4, V/3, postoral ventral cirri; V/2, VI/2, pretransverse ventral cirri; IV/1, V/1, VI/1, transverse cirri; 1–6, dorsal kineties 1–6. Scale bars = 10 µm (b) and 50 µm (a, c, d)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5029371" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5029371/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="2474">Figures 1</figureCitation>
(c,d) and 2(k,l); 
<tableCitation id="C6F00311FFD003450218FDBE964BAE12" box="[285,372,568,593]" captionStart="Table 1" captionStartId="6.[160,216,142,165]" captionText="Table 1. Morphometric data of Sterkiella paratricirrata n. sp." pageId="4" pageNumber="2474">Table 1</tableCitation>
) and other 
<specimenCount id="9D74FD23FFD00345010DFDBE958EAE12" box="[520,689,568,593]" pageId="4" pageNumber="2474" type="generic" typeStatus="paratype">three paratype</specimenCount>
slides (No. LZ 
<date id="FFCC106AFFD00345005BFDBE94F2AE12" box="[862,973,568,593]" pageId="4" pageNumber="2474" value="1601-11-14">14111601</date>
B–D) have been deposited in the Laboratory of Protozoology, Xi’an Jiaotong University, 
<collectingCountry id="F365763AFFD0034500ADFDDC94D5AE30" box="[936,1002,602,627]" name="China" pageId="4" pageNumber="2474">China</collectingCountry>
. The 
<typeStatus id="54C98808FFD003450725FDDC93BDAE30" box="[1056,1154,602,627]" pageId="4" pageNumber="2474">holotype</typeStatus>
specimen was marked on the back of the slides, following 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE34B5BFFD003450013FDFB9494AED5" author="Aescht E" box="[790,939,637,662]" pageId="4" pageNumber="2474" pagination="125 - 234" refId="ref7875" refString="Aescht E. 2008. Annotated catalogue of &quot; type material &quot; of ciliates (Ciliophora) and some further protists at the Upper Austrian Museum in Linz (Austria) including a guideline for &quot; typification &quot; of species. Denisia. 23: 125 - 234." type="journal article" year="2008">Aescht (2008)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE34B5BFFD0034500DAFDFB93BBAED5" author="Foissner W" box="[991,1156,637,662]" pageId="4" pageNumber="2474" pagination="271 - 292" refId="ref8386" refString="Foissner W. 2014. An update of ' basic light and scanning electron microscopic methods for taxonomic studies of ciliated protozoa'. Int J Syst Evol Microbiol. 64: 271 - 292. doi: 10.1099 / ijs. 0.057893 - 0." type="journal article" year="2014">Foissner (2014)</bibRefCitation>
for the labelling of the slides.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3686521FFD0034503A5FD6F9652AF28" pageId="4" pageNumber="2474" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BCD36AAFFD0034503A5FD6F9622AF40" blockId="4.[160,1156,745,875]" box="[160,285,745,771]" pageId="4" pageNumber="2474">
<emphasis id="B906EAB8FFD0034503A5FD6F9622AF40" bold="true" box="[160,285,745,771]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="2474">Etymology</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCD36AAFFD0034503A5FC8B9652AF28" blockId="4.[160,1156,745,875]" pageId="4" pageNumber="2474">
The species-group name ‘ 
<taxonomicName id="4C724D29FFD0034502D4FC8B955EAF65" authorityName="Wang &amp; Lyu &amp; Shao" authorityYear="2021" box="[465,609,781,806]" class="Hypotrichea" family="Oxytrichidae" genus="Sterkiella" kingdom="Protozoa" order="Oxytrichida" pageId="4" pageNumber="2474" phylum="Ciliophora" rank="species" species="paratricirrata">
<emphasis id="B906EAB8FFD0034502D4FC8B955EAF65" box="[465,609,781,806]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="2474">paratricirrata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
’ is a composite of the Greek adjective ‘para-’ (beside or like) and the species-group name ‘ 
<taxonomicName id="4C724D29FFD0034501C3FCA9941CAF0B" authorityName="Berger" authorityYear="1999" baseAuthorityName="Buitkamp" baseAuthorityYear="1977" box="[710,803,815,840]" class="Hypotrichea" family="Oxytrichidae" genus="Sterkiella" kingdom="Protozoa" order="Oxytrichida" pageId="4" pageNumber="2474" phylum="Ciliophora" rank="species" species="tricirrata">
<emphasis id="B906EAB8FFD0034501C3FCA9941CAF0B" box="[710,803,815,840]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="2474">tricirrata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
’, meaning a ciliate similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C724D29FFD0034503A5FCD49659AF28" authorityName="Berger" authorityYear="1999" baseAuthorityName="Buitkamp" baseAuthorityYear="1977" box="[160,358,850,875]" class="Hypotrichea" family="Oxytrichidae" genus="Sterkiella" kingdom="Protozoa" order="Oxytrichida" pageId="4" pageNumber="2474" phylum="Ciliophora" rank="species" species="tricirrata">
<emphasis id="B906EAB8FFD0034503A5FCD49659AF28" box="[160,358,850,875]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="2474">Sterkiella tricirrata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
